opag (0.6.2-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release:
    - Generated C++ code can be put into a namespace.
    - Single character variants of most command line options are
      available.

 -- Martin Dickopp <martin-opag@zero-based.org>  Thu, 20 May 2004 12:09:15 +0200

opag (0.6.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release:
    - The name of the parsing function can be chosen with a command line
      option.
    - When generating C++ code, the name of the exception thrown in the
      case of an error can be specified with a command line option.

 -- Martin Dickopp <martin-opag@zero-based.org>  Sun,  7 Mar 2004 13:17:46 +0100

opag (0.6.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release:
    - It is possible to generate C++ code instead of C code.
    - Option and argument variables are now initialized to zero.
    - Minor bug fixes.
    - Minor spelling mistakes in the manual page corrected.

 -- Martin Dickopp <martin-opag@zero-based.org>  Tue, 17 Feb 2004 15:31:22 +0100

